<TITLE> Forecast remains gloomy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 26 (bdnews24.com)  The whole country including the capital saw continuing rains coupled with gusty winds on Sunday, under the impact of a depression over the Bay of Bengal. The forecast remains gloomy for the next two to three days, says the weather office, on duty meteorologist at the weather office Md Sanwar Haque Mondol told bdnews24.com "But temperatures are not likely to fall much further," he said. The depression over the west central and adjoining northwest Bay moved slightly northwards towards the West Bengal-Bangladesh coasts, intensifying further, said a special bulletin of the met office Sunday morning. The weather office said squally weather may continue over the coastal areas of Bangladesh, with the sea remaining moderate to rough. It has asked Cox's Bazar, Mongla and Chittagong seaports to keep hoisted local cautionary signal number 3. All fishing boats and trawlers in the Bay of Bengal should remain near the coast and move cautiously until advised otherwise. bdnew
